**Analysis of the Main (Target) Image**

The target consists of two separate “towers,” for a total of **16** blocks:

• **Left Tower (9 blocks)**
  1) **Bottom layer:** three red arch‐style blocks side by side.  
  2) **Second layer:** one red arch block in the center (above the middle arch below) with a short green rectangular block set just behind it.  
  3) **Third layer:** two tall green “column” blocks standing side by side on top of (and spanning) the red arch.  
  4) **Fourth layer:** one wide yellow rectangular block bridging the tops of the two green columns.  
  5) **Top piece:** an orange wedge forming a roof.

• **Right Tower (7 blocks)**
  1) **Bottom layer:** one large red arch block.  
  2) **Above that:** a short green rectangular block.  
  3) **Middle layer:** two yellow half‐cylinders side by side.  
  4) **Next layer:** another short green rectangular block.  
  5) **Top layer:** a red arch block enclosing a small green rectangular block in its opening.

Although each “tower” has multiple visible “tiers,” in total you see 16 distinct blocks.

---

## Matching Blocks From the Dictionary

Below is exactly which dictionary‐index block is used (and how many times).  No rotation other than what is shown in the dictionary was allowed.

• **Red arch with underside curved** (Index 1): 3× for the base of the left tower  
• **Red arch (“tunnel”)** (Index 3): 2× total  
  - 1× for the mid‐layer arch in the left tower  
  - 1× for the bottom arch of the right tower  
• **Red arch (“tunnel”)** (Index 4): 1× for the top arch of the right tower  
• **Green short rectangular block** (Index 5): 1× (behind the mid‐arch in the left tower)  
• **Green short rectangular block** (Index 6): 3× (all in the right tower: one under the yellow half‐cylinders, one above them, one inside the top arch)  
• **Tall green column** (Index 7): 2× (the two upright columns atop the left tower’s mid‐arch)  
• **Wide yellow rectangular block** (Index 9): 1× (the “cap” on the left tower)  
• **Yellow half‐cylinder** (Index 10): 2× (the pair in the middle of the right tower)  
• **Orange wedge** (Index 15): 1× (the roof piece on top of the left tower)

---

## Assembly‐Order Instructions

Below is one possible step‐by‐step order to place each block (you may of course build each “tower” in slightly different sequences):

{
  Step1:  Move block with index 1  
  Step2:  Move block with index 1  
  Step3:  Move block with index 1  
  Step4:  Move block with index 5  
  Step5:  Move block with index 3  
  Step6:  Move block with index 7  
  Step7:  Move block with index 7  
  Step8:  Move block with index 9  
  Step9:  Move block with index 15  
  Step10: Move block with index 3  
  Step11: Move block with index 6  
  Step12: Move block with index 10  
  Step13: Move block with index 10  
  Step14: Move block with index 6  
  Step15: Move block with index 4  
  Step16: Move block with index 6  
}
